column5: "Cumberbun" is an excellent storage device Terry! LOL HH

I guess you could hang some baits off of it.  Maybe bettter for putting some plastics and worms.  Thoses hooks might hanging a bit too low and could cause damage where you don't want it, if you know what I mean.
good report. some nice fish there!  Cheers!
Nice goin, Terry.  Thanks for posting those pictures.

I have been fishing the kawarthas lately walleye fishing has been slow but the muskie fishing has been great  well great for the people I have been fishing with, I haven't been catching too many I didn't get his permission to post  picture     went to scugog, I always get walleye there.nope dead carp everywhere and no fish    Saturday we hit a kawartha lake.We trolled we threw jigs in the weeds we casted crank baits and nothing I put on a worm harness and we trolled and the walleye started biting and bitting ..it was a great day on the water..when I ran out of worms I tried plastic worms but that didn't work..switched to crank baits and only caught one more fish  so find weeds slow troll a worm harness catch fish..sounds easy to me     sometimes going old school is the only way to get them               I'm sure that's enough pictures..but there are more
Great pics and report Terry!!! just one question? What's a worm harness?... and how do you get a bridle in thier tiny little mouths???

Looks like a great day on the water Terry. Some real nice fish there! Gotta catch me a musky someday.    What's a worm harness?... and how do you get a bridle in their tiny little mouths??? Ha ha Glen.
Nice shirt!
dress for success ..hey it's light cool and keeps the uv off me   I buy my worms from a tack shop prerigged
Now why didn't I think of that!!!?
Nice going Terry!  Some great looking fish.
Nice fish Terry, Those eyes look yummy.
Great stuff Terry, nice fish.
nice ski and eyes great report
Thanks, fer sharin. I almost fell off my seat when you wrote you always catch Walleyes when you go to Skugog!
If I had a face like that I wouldn't let you post my picture unless I had a fish like that.
Great job Terry. Thanks for all the pics and report.

thanks guys well yeah that's why I didn't get permission to post his picture...LOL   they are yummy but we let all the fish go... I might keep a couple of small walleye to eat a little later in the year
Looks like a great day of fishing Terry.  Good going  Joey
Nice 'Eyes' Terry!
Good to see you get out Terry but you should leave your work clothes at home  MTP
Hey it,s ok to post my face.LOL'  Nice report and nice fish,es bud. You sure are the travelling fishermen.  TFS
Good stuff Terry, some nice fish there.  Maureen
Great pics Terry!  He's dressed like that because he was fishing in between the ceremony and the reception like any diehard fisherman would!
Great report Terry!  Getting out on the water with amazing weather is awesome and you even caught a few fish!  Heard about that Scugog carp thing too...hope the smell wasn't too bad!!!
Nice report Terry.
dang what is wrong with he shirt I wear  do I need to run out and buy some polo shirts
Nice report Terry and good catchin! Don't worry about the shirt comments... none of them have a tie that will go with it anyway! LOL (You could borrow Irishfield's thought!) HH
what that aeroplane tie.........I would even roll over in my grave if they put that on me to bury me........  but no tie in my future trips maybe a cumber bun
